The paper discusses the development of an integrated defense mechanism for intrusion prevention in a software-defined Internet-of-Things (IoT) network. This involves the use of cyberdeception and moving target defense technologies, which are relevant to the fields of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
